<stack-static>
    <statement><p><p>Factorise the following quadratic expression completely:
<me>
{x^2-9 x+20}
</me>
</p>

<p><fillin characters="15" name="ans1"/>  </p></p></statement>
    <solution><p><h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>
We want to factorise:
</p>

<p>
<me>
{x^2-9 x+20}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 1: Identify the coefficients.
</p>

<p>
Coefficient of <m>x</m> = <m>{-9}</m>
</p>

<p>
Constant term = <m>{20}</m>
</p>

<p>
Step 2: Find two numbers whose product is <m>{20}</m> and whose sum is <m>{-9}</m>.
</p>

<p>
The numbers are <m>{4}</m> and <m>{5}</m>, since:
</p>

<p>
<me>
{4} \times {5} = {20}
</me>
</p>

<p>
<me>
-{4} + (-{5}) = {-9}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 3: Write the factorisation.
</p>

<p>
<me>
(x - {4})(x - {5})
</me>
</p></p></solution>
    <answer><p><m>\left(x-5\right) \left(x-4\right)</m></p></answer>
</stack-static>